prospects.name: Aerobic Run 30
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

This is an easy, fun, and unstructured run designed to keep your system ticking over without adding too much fatigue. Make it a priority to never go above Z2, and a good way to do this is to go for a run with a friend and keep it at a conversational pace (or talk to yourself!).

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see this article.

​

**Warm-Up**

NA

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 1

Rest Between Sets: NA

Interval Duration: 30 minutes

Interval Effort: RPE 2-4 -- 145-120% of RTP --HR 70-87% (Z2)

Recovery: NA

​

**Cool Down**

NA

prospects.name: 3 x 1K Building
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z2)

​

**Activation 1: Drills of choice: butt kicks, high knees, builds, strides**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 30s

Interval Distance: 50m each

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 2 minutes

Interval Distance Per Set: 1K

**Interval Effort**

First 1K: RPE 4-5 --120% of RTP --HR 87% (Z2-Z3)

Second 1K: RPE 6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 95% (Z3)

Third 1K: RPE 7+ --100-105% of RTP --HR 95-105% (Z4a-Z4b)

Recovery: RPE 1-2 -->145% RTP --HR <70% (Z1)

​

**Cool Down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

prospects.name: Tempo: 1 x 15
prospects.description:
The meat and potatoes of this 45-minute run is the 15 minutes at steady state tempo effort. A tempo effort is like the stepping stone between endurance and threshold pace. It's "comfortably uncomfortable," meaning that you can maintain that pace for at least an hour and feels like a 6 on the Suffer scale of 1-10. You're below threshold but still generating enough lactic acid that your body is working at and becoming more proficient at clearing it out while in an aerobic state.

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm-Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 120-145% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z1-Z2)

​

**Activation 1: Drills**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance: 25m each: butt kicks, high knees, Carioca, skipping

​

**Main Effort:**

Number of Sets: 1

Interval: 15 minutes

Interval Effort: RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3)

Recovery: RPE <2 -->145% of RTP --HR<70% (Z1)

​

**Cool-down:**

End your workout with 5-10 minutes of easy jogging (Z1)

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

prospects.name: Recovery Run
prospects.description:
This is as easy as easy gets.

You should hardly be going fast enough to consider this a jog.

You want to focus on taking very short strides but keeping your stride rate at least 80 steps per minute.

You should be embarrassed to be seen going this slowly!

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm-Up **NA

​

**Main Effort** 

Number of Sets 1 

Rest Between Sets: NA 

Interval Repeats Per Set NA 

Interval Effort: 20 minutes @ RPE 1-3 -- 165-140% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1) 

Recovery: NA

​

**Extra Volume** NA

​

**Cool Down** NA

prospects.name: 3 x 2K Tempo
prospects.description:
Make sure to keep a lid on your desire to go fast and keep the pace capped at Z3/tempo effort. This workout is NOT about speed!

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm-Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 1-2 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR <70-87% (Z1)

​

**Activation 1: Drills: Butt kicks, high knees, builds, carioca, strides & skipping**

Number of Sets: 2 each

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance Per Set: 25-50m each

Interval Effort: RPE 3-4 (Z2)

Recovery: RPE <2 (Z1)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 4 minutes

Interval Distance Per Set: 2K

Interval Effort: RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3)

Recovery: RPE <2 -->145% of RTP --HR<70% (Z1)

​

**Cool Down**

5 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

​

prospects.name: 4 x 90 seconds Running Up Hill 4-7% Gradient
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warmup**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 (Z1-Z2)

​

**Activation 1 10-second accelerations**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 30s

Interval Effort: Build from 145% of RTP to 100% RTP (Z2-Z4b)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 4

Rest Between Sets: 4 minutes

Recovery Effort: RPE 2-4 (Z1-Z2)

Interval Duration: 90 seconds @ Gradient 4-7%

Interval Effort: RPE 8.5-9.5 --92-85% of RTP --HR 105% + (Z5)

​

**Cool down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- >145% of RTP -- <70% of RTHR (Z1)

prospects.name: 4 x 1K Kicking
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 1-2 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR <70-87% (Z1-Z2)

​

**Activation 1**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 30s

Interval Distance Per Set: 75m sprint

Interval Effort: RPE 10 --<85% of RTP --HR NA (Z6) Recovery RPE <2 -->145% of RTP --HR <70% (Z1)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 4

Rest Between Sets: 3 minutes

Interval Distance Per set: 1K

Interval Effort: 900m @ RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3) Final 100m @ RPE 10 --<85% of RTP --HR 105% (Z6)

Recovery: RPE 1-2 --<145% of RTP --HR <70% (Z1)

Note: Pace it so that you are increasing your speed for the last 100m and not slowing at the end.

​

**Cool Down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

prospects.name: 3 x 1.5K Increasing
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

If you drill into the pacing strategies of any endurance competitor, you quickly learn that the negative split is the fastest way to complete a course. A negative split is where your pace is higher during the second half of the course. The goal of this workout is to practice that pacing strategy today.

​

**Warm-up**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 120-145% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z2)

​

**Activation 1: Drills of choice: butt kicks, high knees, etc.**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance: 50m

**Activation 2: 150-200m Strides**

Number of Sets: 2-3

Rest Between Sets: 30-sec

Interval Effort: 110-100% RTP (Z4a)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 3 minutes

Interval Distance Per Set: 1.5K

Interval Effort:

Begin @ RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3)

Steadily increase to RPE 7.5 over the entire distance -- 100-92% of RTP--HR 100-105% (Z4a)

\*Strive to achieve the same pace across all three efforts.

​

**Cool-down:**

Walk or jog for 5-10 minutes to cool down (Z1)

​

prospects.name: 4 x 5: Threshold
prospects.description:
Be very careful when executing this session! Your desire to suffer is strong and the short duration of these intervals will tempt you to push the intensity over your threshold target on this workout. After all, your LT pace is one that you can hold for about an hour, so running at that pace for only 5 minutes is going to feel too easy...and you don't like easy...so make a commitment to stay true to the intensity target that is prescribed.

​

Some reasons for doing short threshold intensity efforts are: to improve recovery time and the ability to repeat the effort after a short rest period, and to do quality work efforts without generating a lot of fatigue that requires significant recovery.

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warmup**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-3 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1-2)

​

**Activation**

2 x 100m accelerations with 1 minute recovery (jog or walk back to start) in between

​

**Main effort**

Number of Sets: 4

Interval Duration: 5 minutes

Interval Intensity: 10k pace (RPE 6.5-7 -- 100-110% of RTP -- HR 95-100%) (Z4a)

Recovery duration and intensity: 3 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 120-145% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z2)

When you can no longer keep the pace, the workout is over.

​

**Cool Down**

3-5 minutes @ RPE 2-3 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1-2)
